title: City-County Council Committee Meeting - Admin and Finance

tags.name: Make Comments In Support Of Urban Forests

description:
We need your voice!

This week the Indianapolis City-County Council revealed its "spring fiscal" - spending outside the regular budget process. We were encouraged to see $1 Million allocated to the purchase of urban forests - a huge step forward. However, these allocations aren't set in stone.

The "spring fiscal" will now be reviewed by the Administration and Finance Committee on Tuesday May 13th. If they recommend the proposal, a final vote will be held on June 9th. At the suggestion of Councilor Boots, we are asking supporters to make public comment in support of these funds for urban forests. Councilors on this committee will inform the impending budget process and in this way our comments will be doubly useful.

description:

We will meet at the entrance to the forest on 33rd Pl & Gainesville St. SE at 9am. We will spend the first 30 minutes doing introductions and training, then we will remove vines until about 12pm. We will focus on non-native invasive vines including porcelainberry (Ampelopsis glandulosa var. brevipedunculata) and English ivy (Hedera helix).

Please wear long pants, long sleeves, and close-toed shoes. Instructions and tools will be provided, so just bring yourself and a good attitude!

A reminder email will be sent out the day before with detailed instructions on where to meet.

title: Invasive Vine Removal/Canvassing in Riverdale Park

sponsor.name: Chesapeake Climate Action Network / Action Fund

description:
Join the Riverdale Park Green Team to canvass and remove Invasive Vines around the Riverdale Park neighborhood.

This event will be a fun mix of door-to-door canvassing and invasive vine removal. We will meet at Riverside Drive Park and spend 30 minutes doing training on vine removal and canvassing. From there we will break into pairs and head to a list of pre-surveyed residences in the area to offer vine removal for residents.

We will focus on non-native invasive vines including porcelainberry (Ampelopsis glandulosa var. brevipedunculata) and English ivy (Hedera helix). Please wear long pants, long sleeves, and close-toed shoes. Instructions and tools will be provided, so just bring yourself and a good attitude!

A reminder email will be sent out the day before with detailed instructions on where to meet.

Students under the age of 16 must be accompanied by a parent/guardian for the duration of the event.

location.venue: Staten Island Office of Rep. Nicole Malliotakis

description:
Join us outside the Staten Island office of Rep. Nicole Malliotakis to speak out against Republican attacks on healthcare. Come make your voice heard. Share your personal story and thoughts.

Congress is quickly moving to try to take away our health care and other basic human needs programs in order to give EVEN MORE HUGE tax cuts for billionaires and big corporations. We can't let that happen, and YOUR voice will make a big difference.

What's at stake?

Medicaid
Affordable Care Act (ACA)
Hospitals and nursing homes
Community health centers and home care programs
Health care for 9-11 first responders
Veterans Administration health care programs
SNAP (Food Stamps)
Meals-on-Wheels
School breakfasts and lunches
Senior centers
Head Start
Public schools
Student loans and grants
Housing vouchers
Public housing
...and SO much more!
Nicole Malliotakis sits on one of the key committees that is writing up an important budget bill that will create massive tax giveaways to special interests and the ultra-rich. Instead, we need her to make them "pay what they owe" and "pay their fair share" of taxes, just like all the rest of us do, so that we can ALL have good public programs that serve everyone!

Nicole Malliotakis has said she will fight to protect Medicaid for some people (but not for everyone.) We need her to also stand up for health care for regular, everyday low-income workers and our families, not just publicly-sympathetic people like seniors, children, people with disabilities, and pregnant women.

Join with your neighbors on Staten Island to give Nicole Malliotakis a piece of your mind about what she and Congress are doing!

title: Tell Camden City Council: No Vote on Rushed EMR Agreement!
description:
On Tuesday, May 13, Camden City council is planning to try and rush through a Memorandum of Understanding (MOU) with EMR, the scrap metal recycling facility that recently caught fire-- the company's 6th fire in recent years-- polluting the air and putting residents' health at risk. 

**Please join us in telling city council to stop this rushed vote!**

Community organizers have requested copies of this MOU that is being presented at the council meeting and have been told a public version of the agreement is not available. *The public has not been adequately in the decision making process.* It's unclear how this particular dollar amount was arrived at. **The MOU does not go far enough in protecting the public and holding EMR accountable. **

Let's pack this city council meeting and let council members know that they cannot rush through a MOU to try and pacify the public who are rightfully angry at EMR and the electeds who are not doing all they can to protect public health. 

Bring your signs and your friends! Let's tell them NO VOTE on this rushed MOU!
